# Implement Ledger UI Layer

The goal is to implement the presentation layer for the Ledger feature, allowing users to view balances for all clients and vendors, see transaction details, and add new ledger entries.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The Ledger Homepage will display two distinct sections for Clients and Vendors, each with its own "Add Entry" button as requested.
> Balances will be color-coded: Green for Clients and Red for Vendors.

## Proposed Changes

### Ledger Feature

#### [NEW] [add_ledger_entry_dialog.dart](file:///home/waleedqamar/Documents/ledgerly/lib/features/ledger/presentation/widgets/add_ledger_entry_dialog.dart)
Common dialog to add a new ledger entry. It will accept an optional pre-selected party.

#### [NEW] [ledger_page.dart](file:///home/waleedqamar/Documents/ledgerly/lib/features/ledger/presentation/pages/ledger_page.dart)
Main Ledger homepage showing lists of clients and vendors with their balances.

#### [NEW] [ledger_details_page.dart](file:///home/waleedqamar/Documents/ledgerly/lib/features/ledger/presentation/pages/ledger_details_page.dart)
Shows a list of all transactions for a specific party.

## Open Questions

- Should the balance shown on the homepage be the "Running Balance" (Total Credit - Total Debit) or something else?
- For "Add Entry", should I auto-generate an invoice number if none is provided, or is it mandatory? (The entity has `required String invoiceNumber`)

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Since this is a UI task, I will perform manual verification using the browser if possible, or ensure the code follows the established patterns in `vendor_dashboard_view.dart`.

### Manual Verification
- Verify that the Ledger page shows both clients and vendors.
- Verify that the "Add Entry" button opens the dialog.
- Verify that clicking a party navigates to the details page with correct transactions.
- Verify color coding (Vendors: Red, Clients: Green).
